1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:26,583
Prayer to Saint Sergius of Radonezh Pray slowly. Read with attention.

2
00:00:26,583 --> 00:00:37,390
O Holy Father Sergius, you sought the quiet of the forest to devote your life entirely to God. Facing cold, hunger, and wild beasts, you worked with your own hands, building

3
00:00:37,390 --> 00:00:48,197
a simple church in honor of the Holy Trinity. By your prayers, the wilderness became a spiritual garden, drawing disciples from all lands.

4
00:00:48,197 --> 00:00:58,795
O wise patron, we remember how you struggled as a child to read and write, and how the Lord granted you the gift of understanding through the prayers of a holy monk. Look

5
00:00:58,795 --> 00:01:09,393
upon students and all who face difficulties in learning. Intercede for them, that the Lord may open their minds to understand wisdom and use it for His glory.

6
00:01:09,393 --> 00:01:20,514
O meek father, you refused all earthly honors and sought only the unity and peace of the land. In times of division and violence, you reconciled princes and brought peace

7
00:01:20,514 --> 00:01:31,634
to divided communities. Pray for us, that the spirit of peace may dwell in our homes, churches, and nations, casting out all hatred and division.

8
00:01:31,634 --> 00:01:40,211
Teach us, O holy abbot, the value of humility, labor, and spiritual watchfulness. Help us to guard our minds against pride, to accept our weaknesses with hope, and to walk in

9
00:01:40,211 --> 00:01:48,787
the light of sincere repentance, always seeking the grace of the Holy Trinity.

10
00:01:48,787 --> 00:01:59,648
Saint Sergius of Radonezh, pray to God for us. Amen.

